Training Fasted vs Training Fed (READ üëá)
.
For the first time in a long time I trained fed today (had a meal before my workout) Unsurprisingly to me, it wasn‚Äôt a great sesh.
.
I have been training fasted (first thing in the morning) for years. I feel strongest in the morning and I‚Äôm super focused so this works best for me.
.
This is how you should approach training. How do you feel best? Fed/Fasted? What time do you feel best? AM/Midday/Evening
.
Everyone is different and there is no cookie cutter ideal for all of us. Learn to listen to your body and experiment with different times/different pre workout meals/non meals.
.
Unless you‚Äôre training to be Mr Olympia, you don‚Äôt need to worry about meal timing. It won‚Äôt impact you as much as a bad sesh at the gym will.
.
So get that mentality of ‚ÄúI need to eat to fuel my workout‚Äù and ‚ÄúI gotta eat something every 3 hours or I‚Äôll shrivel up into a raisin‚Äù out of your head.
.
Again, for 99.99% of us this won‚Äôt have any impact on our goals, and will more than likely cause you to get super frustrated when you miss that one meal/shake whatever.
.
Keep it simple! Focus on hitting your macro target for the day, and train when/how you feel strongest. That‚Äôs it. Don‚Äôt over complicate it.
.

SET BIG GOALS (read üëá)
.
Road to a 500lb bench press started today for me with a 5x5 at 345.
.
After coming in a month early on my 405 bench press goal for 2019, I‚Äôm taking advantage of this month by looking forward to bigger things.
.
I know people will think I‚Äôm crazy for setting such a big goal and they‚Äôll give me a million reasons why I won‚Äôt get there, but that‚Äôs just a lot of noise.
.
You are capable of so much more than you think and 10x more than what other people think.
.
For 2020 set some big goals!!!
.
Wanna lose 100lbs? Do it!
.
Wanna add 100lbs to your deadlift? Do it!
.
*** All things are possible, BUT (big fat but) you have to be willing to COMMIT EVERY DAY towards achieving that goal.
.
It‚Äôs not gonna happen in a month, or by putting in some crazy effort for two months, it‚Äôs gonna happen by CONSISTENTLY achieving your tasks day after day.
.
Keep this in mind! It‚Äôs not that one huge swing of the axe that brings the tree down it‚Äôs the thousands of small hacks over and over that get the job done.
.
Hope this motivates you guys to get your ass outta bed this Sunday! Get after it!
.

Flex on em
.
Whenever you‚Äôre setting out to achieve big things, you‚Äôll have lots of people who will come and tell you all the reasons why your goal is too big, out of reach and blah blah blah.
.
The thing is, those people and their opinions ARE IRRELEVANT to your success.
.
You have the choice to:
.
A) Listen to those people who have absolutely no impact on your success and let your fear of failure and their opinions paralyze you.
.
B) Hit the mute button on those people, put the blinders on and be RELENTLESS in your pursuit. (Ultimately leading to your success)
.
It‚Äôs all on you, ALWAYS. So stop pointing fingers.
.
Let people talk, let people have their doubts, it MEANS NOTHING.
.
You have unlimited potential to achieve all things. Have faith, keep persevering and never give up.
.

Although I don‚Äôt feel like I am exactly where I want to be, I‚Äôve made it a long way and I realize now the REAL victory is that I understand that I AM IN CONTROL and EVERY STEP I take matters! üö® Road to 405 continues with a new 385 PR .
ü•û 385 felt nice and buttery but I didn‚Äôt want to push 405 today. Finished up the push day workout as planned and have my sights set on 405 for Turkey Day.

‚ùóÔ∏èIt‚Äôs important to warm up properly when attempting a one rep max. It took me a long time to figure out a balance between getting a good warm up and saving energy for the main event.
.
‚úÖHere is what I found works best. Bookmark this and use it the next time you are attempting a one rep max.
.
‚úèÔ∏è Warming up for a one rep max
.
Set 1 
50-60% of 1 rep max attempt for 5 reps 2-3 minute rest
.
Set 2
70% of 1 rep max attempt for 3 reps
2-3 minute rest
.
Set 3
80% of 1 rep max attempt for 1 rep
3-5 minute rest
.
Set 4
90% of 1 rep max attempt for 1 rep
5 minute rest
.
Set 5
One rep max attempt
.
üôè Hope this helps you guys if you‚Äôve been a bit lost with how to ramp up for a PR attempt.
.
